  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Header associations:</strong> Data cells are automatically associated with their column and row headers through the table structure</li>
      <li><strong>Screen reader navigation:</strong> When navigating to a td, screen readers announce the associated headers</li>
      <li><strong>Complex tables:</strong> For tables where automatic association is insufficient, use the <code>headers</code> attribute</li>
      <li><strong>Avoid empty cells:</strong> Use meaningful placeholders like "N/A" or "-" for better screen reader experience</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>The headers Attribute</h3>
    <p>For complex tables with multiple levels of headers, explicitly associate data cells with their headers:</p>

